@ENDNODE

@NODE TIPS_TROUBLESHOOTING "Tips & Troubleshooting"
@PREV RESTORING_BACKUPS
@NEXT CREDITS_VERSION_INFO
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Tips & Troubleshooting@{UB}@{APEN 1}
======================


@{APEN 2}GENERAL TIPS@{APEN 1}
------------

- @{B}Enable backups for big runs:@{UB} If you're tidying a lot of folders
  (especially with recursion enabled), turning on backups gives you a
  way back if you don't like the result.
- @{B}Start small:@{UB} Try a single drawer first so you can see how the settings
  affect icon layout and window sizing before you point it at a whole
  partition.
- @{B}Save your settings:@{UB} Once you've found a setup you like, use @{B}Save
  Settings@{UB} from the menu so you can load it again later.
- @{B}Live preview trick:@{UB} Keep a drawer window open while you run iTidy on
  that same drawer. You can quickly see how the layout looks and tweak
  settings before doing a long recursive run. While iTidy is working
  through a drawer, icons can briefly overlap until it has repositioned
  everything. For best results, let it finish the current drawer before
  cancelling. Once a drawer is complete, it's generally safe to stop a
  long run if you've seen enough. Workbench may cache window
  sizing/position until you close and reopen the drawer, but icon
  placement can be checked straight away.
- @{B}To see window changes clearly:@{UB} Close any drawers you're tidying before
  you run iTidy. After it finishes, you may need to restart Workbench
  (or reboot) to see updated window sizes and positions everywhere.


@{APEN 2}ICONS APPEAR MISALIGNED@{APEN 1}
-----------------------

If some icons look misaligned after tidying while others look fine, it's
often down to icon.library support rather than iTidy itself.

On Workbench 3.0/3.1 with older icon.library versions, OS3.5+ colour icons
may not render at their real size and can appear as tiny placeholder
images. iTidy positions icons using the @{I}actual@{UI} icon dimensions, but
Workbench may draw them at the wrong size, which makes the layout look
"off".

@{B}What to do:@{UB}

- Update icon.library to v44+ if you want to use OS3.5+ colour icons
  (typically via OS3.5/3.9/3.2, or an updated library from Aminet).
- Alternatively, convert colour icons back to NewIcons or classic icons
  if you're keeping a more stock 3.0/3.1 setup.


@{APEN 2}WINDOW POSITIONS NOT UPDATING@{APEN 1}
-----------------------------

If you restore a backup (or run iTidy) and window positions don't appear
to change right away, this is usually Workbench caching.

@{B}What to do:@{UB}

- Close and reopen the affected drawer windows.
- If it still doesn't look updated, restart Workbench or reboot.


@{APEN 2}IF BACKUP OR RESTORE DOESN'T WORK AS EXPECTED@{APEN 1}
---------------------------------------------

A few quick things to check:

- LhA is installed in "C:"
- You have enough free disk space for archives (backups) or extraction
  (restores)
- The original folder paths still exist when restoring
- Check "PROGDIR:logs/" for any error details


@{APEN 2}SLOW PROCESSING ON LARGE FOLDER TREES@{APEN 1}
-------------------------------------

Recursing through thousands of folders takes time on real hardware,
especially with mechanical drives.

A few tips:

- It's fine to leave iTidy running unattended during large jobs.
- Avoid running other disk-heavy tasks at the same time.
- If you're doing a huge collection, it can be quicker (and safer) to
  work in chunks (for example "WHDLoad:Games" first, then
  "WHDLoad:Demos") rather than doing everything in one run.


@{APEN 2}ICONS AREN'T MOVED, AND THE PROGRESS LOG SHOWS NO ICONS FOUND.@{APEN 1}
--------------------------------------------------------------

Check the folder in Workbench and see if the menu "Window->Show->All
Files" is selected. This option shows the contents of the folder by giving
each item a temporary icon, which won't be visible to iTidy.

If you want iTidy to tidy this folder, you should create real icons first.
Select the folder's contents via "Window->Select Contents", then choose
"Icons->Snapshot". Default icons will be created, and iTidy will be able
to process them.


@{APEN 2}ITIDY IS SKIPPING SOME FOLDERS THAT CONTAIN VALID ICONS@{APEN 1}
-------------------------------------------------------

By default, iTidy will skip processing folders if the parent folder
doesn't have an icon.

To bypass this, go to Advanced Settings and untick "Skip hidden folders"


@{APEN 2}ICONS DON'T OPEN ("UNABLE TO OPEN YOUR TOOL")@{APEN 1}
---------------------------------------------

This usually means an icon's Default Tool points to something that isn't
installed on your system.

@{B}What to do:@{UB}

- Use @{B}Fix Default Tools...@{UB} to scan for missing tools and repair them.
- See the Default Tool Analysis section for how the scanner works.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


@{APEN 2}SAFETY & DISCLAIMER@{APEN 1}
-------------------

iTidy is free hobby software that I work on in my spare time. It's been
tested on real Amiga systems, but it may still have bugs or edge cases I
haven't run into yet.

iTidy only touches ".info" files and Workbench drawer/window layout
information. It also includes an optional backup system to help roll back
changes, but you shouldn't treat that as a replacement for your own
regular system backups (and it's still being improved).

If you use iTidy, you do so at your own risk. I can't accept
responsibility for data loss, corruption, or any other damage caused by
using (or misusing) the software.

Before running iTidy for the first time - especially on large or important
partitions - make sure you have a current, verified backup. If you want to
be extra cautious, try it on a small test folder or a copy of your
Workbench setup first.

